- `likely`: tested [here](https://github.com/apache/tvm/blob/bb513866ad70fa20eb0c37ca339d330d6a76c747/tests/python/unittest/test_tir_schedule_compute_at.py#L849)

output it was the following error:
```
TVMError: Not all Vars are passed in api_args: 'compute' is not bound
to any variables
```

headline: [ETHOSN] Support multiply conversion to depthwise
body:
Multiply can be supported when offloaded to the NPU by a conversion to
a depthwise convolution operation. This is only supported when the
multiply operation has a single single variable input with the other
being a constant of shape [1, ..., C]. This commit adds a new pass
"ConvertEquivalents" (name subject to change) to handle this conversion
before codegen.

Change-Id: If8029373261364ed09fcd921ee71e31877a9125a
author: lhutton1

headline: [LLVM] Add "cl-opt" attribute to target_kind "llvm"
body:
Add LLVMTargetInfo class that can be used to query the LLVM
configuration without forcing an LLVMTarget to be created.

There is no programmatic way to obtain the actual type of an LLVM
option. The type is necessary to obtain the value of the option,
hence it must be provided as a part of the option string.
See src/target/llvm/target_kind.cc for more information about the
syntax.
author: kparzysz-quic
